Key Match Events: Youssef En-Nesyri opened the scoring for Morocco in the 30th minute
Sofiane Boufal scored a second goal five minutes after En-Nesyri's first
En-Nesyri scored his double ten minutes into the second half
Sierra Leone managed to score only once during the first half
Post-Match Reflections: Abde Ezzalzouli urged Moroccan supporters to encourage the players, stating that their support will strengthen the team
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at the Stade Auguste Denise in Cote d’Ivoire
Morocco will play its first competition match on January 17 against Tanzania
The Atlas Lions will compete in Group F alongside Tanzania, DR Congo, and Zambia at the AFCON
Morocco hasn’t won a title since 1976 and was a finalist in 2004
